<entry><media id="eip-id1168469639059" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_03_05_009_img-04.png"/></media></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>Subtract.</entry>
<entry><media id="eip-id1168469846407" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_03_05_009_img-05.png"/></media></entry>
 </row>


</tbody>











</tgroup>
</table></para><para id="fs-id833746">Since <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> results in a true equation, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> is a solution to the equation.</para>
<para id="fs-id1880992"><table id="eip-id1168468223504" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="This figure has 4 rows. The first row is 2 times x minus 5 equals negative 13. The second row states substitute negative 9 for x and has 2 times negative 9 minus 5 equals negative 13 with a question mark above the equal sign. The third row states multiply and has negative 18 minus 5 equals negative 13 with a question mark above the equal sign. The fourth row states subtract and has negative 23 is not equal to negative 13."><label/>
<tgroup cols="2"><tbody>
 <row>
   <entry><span class="token">ⓒ</span> Substitute −9 for x in the equation to determine if it is true.</entry>
<entry/>
</row>
<row>
<entry/>
<entry><media id="eip-id1168469596074" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_03_05_010_img-01.png"/></media></entry>

 </row>
 <row>
  <entry>Substitute −9 for x.</entry>
